# Architecture

- All string literals (command IDs, config keys, view IDs) live in `constants.ts` ‚Äî never hardcode them
- Config reads/writes go through `services/configService.ts` ‚Äî never call `getConfiguration()` directly
- `CypressTestController` owns test discovery, execution, and UI orchestration via the VS Code Testing API
- `cypressRunner.ts` provides pure functions (`buildCommand`, `getEnvironmentVariables`) ‚Äî no state
- `configParser.ts` reads `specPattern` from cypress config files ‚Äî used by `testController` for dynamic extension resolution
- Use `ShellExecution` options for env vars, not string concatenation
- Webviews must have a CSP with a nonce
- See `ROADMAP.md` for the full improvement plan
